        <updateDate>2023-03-15T14:38:37Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Parental Rights Over The Education and Care of Their Kids Act or the PROTECT Kids Act</strong></p> <p>This bill requires elementary and middle schools, as a condition of receiving federal funds, to obtain parental consent under specified circumstances.</p> <p>Specifically, an elementary school or a school consisting of only grades 5-8 must obtain parental consent before (1) changing a minor child's gender markers, pronouns, or preferred name on any school form; or (2) allowing a child to change the child's sex-based accommodations, including locker rooms or bathrooms.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
